Does any one know of a similar XML XSL XPath forum?

I have found very few examples of XPath sum() usage (at least not enough).
I have an XML file that references an XSL file for formatting.  It is 
working.

However, I want to add some group level summation.

The XML file is fairly flat in structure.

My question: Does XPath sum() work with relatively flat XML data trees or 
must they have more levels to represent the grouping levels?

The XSL template file contains three nested &lt;xsl:for-each ...&gt; loops.
The first loop sorts/groups on &lt;key1&gt;, the second on &lt;key1&gt;-&lt;Key2&gt; and the 
third loop on &lt;text1&gt; displaying the corresponding values for &lt;count&gt;.

Existing (flat) XML data tree:
&lt;root&gt;

  &lt;record&gt;
   &lt;key1&gt;A&lt;/key1&gt;
   &lt;key2&gt;1&lt;/key2&gt;
   &lt;text1&gt;text&lt;/text1&gt;
   &lt;count&gt;2&lt;/count&gt;
  &lt;/record&gt;

&lt;/root&gt;

Alternative grouping level XML data tree:
&lt;root&gt;

  &lt;record&gt;
   &lt;key1&gt;A
     &lt;key2&gt;1
       &lt;text1&gt;text
         &lt;count&gt;1&lt;/count&gt;
       &lt;/text1&gt;
     &lt;/key2&gt;
   &lt;/key1&gt;
  &lt;/record&gt;

&lt;/root&gt;

Is trying to sum() with the &#39;flat&#39; XML file futile?
  Or should I spend my efforts to create the alternative XML file?

Suggestions will be appreciated.

                 Clark Anderson
